# Example: Using Claude Code Configs in Your Project

This example shows how to add Claude Code configurations to any development container.

## Simple Example

Create `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` in your project:

```json
{
  "name": "My Risky Experiments",
  "image": "mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/base:ubuntu",

  "features": {
    "ghcr.io/rplsmn/Claude-code-config-sharing/claude-code-configs:1": {}
  }
}
```

Then:
1. Open project in VS Code/Claude Code
2. Click "Reopen in Container"
3. Container starts with Claude configs pre-installed
4. Use slash commands: `/code`, `/review`, `/lead`, etc.

## With Node.js

```json
{
  "name": "Node.js Project",
  "image": "mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/javascript-node:20",

  "features": {
    "ghcr.io/rplsmn/Claude-code-config-sharing/claude-code-configs:1": {}
  },

  "postCreateCommand": "npm install"
}
```

## With Python

```json
{
  "name": "Python Project",
  "image": "mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/python:3.11",

  "features": {
    "ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/git:1": {},
    "ghcr.io/rplsmn/Claude-code-config-sharing/claude-code-configs:1": {}
  },

  "postCreateCommand": "pip install -r requirements.txt"
}
```

## For Podman Users

Configure VS Code to use Podman in `.vscode/settings.json`:

```json
{
  "dev.containers.dockerPath": "podman"
}
```

The same devcontainer.json works with both Docker and Podman!

## Test It

After container starts:
```bash
# Verify installation
ls ~/.claude/commands/

# Try a slash command in Claude Code
# /code
# /review
```

## Benefits

- Install packages recklessly → no risk to host
- Break things → rebuild container
- Consistent Claude setup across all projects
- Same commands in every container
